Russian Equity Movers: Aeroflot, Ulan-Ude Aviation, Uralkali

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n   a n d   M a r k   S w e e t m a n
-- 
2011-05-11T15:27:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-11/russian-equity-movers-ulan-ude-aviation-uralkali-shares-move.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  slid 1.4
percent to 1,654.78 by the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow, reversing
an earlier gain of as much as 0.9 percent. The dollar-
denominated RTS Index lost 1 percent to 1,908.46.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Aeroflot (AFLT RX),  Russia ’s biggest airline, climbed
to its highest level in two weeks, rising 2.3 percent to 68.79
rubles after the company reported a record 1.04 million
passengers in April.  OAO Polymetal (PMTL RX), a Russian silver producer, sank to
its lowest since November, losing 3.1 percent to 480.6 rubles.
Silver futures for July delivery slumped 4.6 percent to $36.72
an ounce on the Comex in  New York , after climbing the previous
two days.  Ulan-Ude Aviation Plant (UUAZ RX) declined 4 percent to
53.79 rubles, its biggest drop in three weeks, after parent
company OAO Russian Helicopters postponed its initial public
offering.  OAO  Uralkali (URKA)   gained for a third day, rising 0.8
percent to 221.4 rubles, as UBS AG upgraded Russia’s second-
biggest potash producer to “buy” from “neutral.” UBS
increased its 2011 potash price forecast 8 percent to $465 per
ton.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jason Corcoran in Moscow at 
